This applies to any of the senses, e.g.,. taste, smell, and sound. Food may no longer be tasty, or a musical experience may no longer be enjoyable. Anhedonia also refers to an inability to feel pleasure related to activities that an affected individual previously derived pleasure from.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Reduced ability of the cornea to respond to stimulation.

definition.value: Corneal sensitivity to touch can be assessed by an aesthesiometer, which measures the corneal touch threshold. Decreased corneal sensation is associated with a decreased corneal reflex (HP:0008000); however, impairment of the corneal reflex can have other causes such as trigeminal nerve compression or a cerebellopontine angle lesion. Well known causes of decreased corneal sensation include Herpes simplex keratitis, neuroparalytic keratitis, leprosy, acoustic neuroma, and absolute glaucoma.

definition.value: The examiner can test for asterixis by asking the patient to extend the arms, spread the fingers, dorsiflex the wrist and observe for the abnormal "flapping" tremor at the wrist. https://w3id.org/babelon/comment.value: label of HP:0012175 (Resistance to activated protein C)  ; abnormality of blood and blood-forming tissues

value.value: 活性化タンパク Cへの抵抗性

"Špatná antikoagulační odpověď na aktivovaný protein C. Plazma se označuje jako ""APC rezistentní"" když přidání exogenního aktivovaného proteinu C neprodlouží koagulační čas v aktivovaném parciálním tomboplastinovém testu."

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Poor anticoagulant response to activated protein C. A plasma is termed 'APC resistant' when the addition of exogenous APC fails to prolong its clotting time in an activated partial thromboplastin time assay.

value.value: Aktive protein C'ye karşı zayıf antikoagülan yanıtı. Aktive olmuş kısmi tromboplastin zamanı (aPTT) deneyinde ekzojen APC eklendiğinde 'APC dirençli' olarak adlandırılan bir plazmanın pıhtılaşma zamanını uzatamamaktadır

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Poor anticoagulant response to activated protein C. A plasma is termed 'APC resistant' when the addition of exogenous APC fails to prolong its clotting time in an activated partial thromboplastin time assay.

value.value: Poor anticoagulant response to activated protein C. A plasma is termed 'APC resistant' when the addition of exogenous APC fails to prolong its clotting time in an activated partial thromboplastin time assay.

definition.value: The protein C pathway is a major anticoagulant mechanism that down-regulates the prothrombin- and intrinsic factor X (FX)-activating complexes via inactivation of their respective cofactors, activated factors V (FVa) and VIII (FVIIIa). Cofactor inactivation occurs by limited proteolysis at certain amino acid positions in FVa and in FVIIIa. These reactions are catalyzed by the serine protease activated protein C (APC) and stimulated by the APC cofactor protein S. Functional defects of the protein C pathway determine a plasma phenotype known as APC resistance, which is a prevalent and important risk factor for venous thrombosis. A plasma is termed 'APC resistant' when the addition of exogenous APC fails to prolong its clotting time in an activated partial thromboplastin time (aPTT) assay.
